&lt;p>The useful part is this:&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&lt;strong>Spark shuffle becomes slow at large scale because reducers read billions of tiny shuffle blocks from disk/network. Magnet fixes that by converting tiny fragmented shuffle blocks into larger merged blocks before reducers fetch them.&lt;/strong>&lt;/p>
&lt;h2 id="core-problem">Core Problem&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>The central problem is not:&lt;/p>
&lt;ul>
&lt;li>“Spark is slow”&lt;/li>
&lt;li>“Network is slow”&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
&lt;p>The real problem is:&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&lt;strong>Tiny random reads.&lt;/strong>&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>System Design Resources</title><link>https://ashishdoneriya.github.io/system-design-resources.html</link><pubDate>Fri, 19 Jun 2026 01:00:00 +0530</pubDate><guid>https://ashishdoneriya.github.io/system-design-resources.html</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="high-level">High Level&lt;/h2>
